---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Personal Loan Interest Rates - Compare All Banks 2026 | TrueCred Loan Expert">

<!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <a href="#">Loans</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <span>Personal Loan Interest Rates</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Personal Loan Interest Rates</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Compare personal loan interest rates across all major banks and NBFCs in India for April 2026. Find the lowest rates starting from 9.98% p.a. and save thousands on your EMIs. Updated daily with the latest offers.</p>
      <div class="hero-highlights">
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-percent"></i>
          <span>Lowest Rate: 9.98% p.a.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-building-columns"></i>
          <span>80+ Lenders Compared</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-clock"></i>
          <span>Updated: April 2026</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page Content -->
  <section class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <div class="content-main">
          <h2>Personal Loan Interest Rates in India — April 2026</h2>
          <p>Personal loan interest rates in India vary significantly across lenders, ranging from 9.98% to 36% p.a. depending on your credit profile, income, employer category, and loan amount. Banks like HDFC, SBI, and ICICI typically offer lower rates to prime customers with high CIBIL scores, while NBFCs and fintech lenders provide more accessible options for applicants with moderate credit histories at slightly higher rates.</p>
          <p>At TrueCred Loan Expert, we compile and update personal loan interest rates from over 80 banks and NBFCs daily to help you make an informed decision. Choosing the right lender can save you ₹20,000 to ₹1,50,000 over the loan tenure. Factors like your CIBIL score, employer category, existing relationship with the bank, loan amount, and tenure all play a role in determining your final interest rate.</p>

          <div class="info-grid">
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">9.98%</span>
              <span class="info-label">Lowest Rate (p.a.)</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">36%</span>
              <span class="info-label">Highest Rate (p.a.)</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">80+</span>
              <span class="info-label">Lenders Compared</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Personal Loan Interest Rates Comparison — April 2026</h3>
          <table class="rate-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Bank / NBFC</th>
                <th>Interest Rate (p.a.)</th>
                <th>Processing Fee</th>
                <th>Max Tenure</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>SBI</td>
                <td>11.00% - 14.00%</td>
                <td>Up to 1.50%</td>
                <td>6 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>HDFC Bank</td>
                <td>10.50% - 21.00%</td>
                <td>Up to 2.50%</td>
                <td>5 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>ICICI Bank</td>
                <td>10.75% - 19.00%</td>
                <td>Up to 2.25%</td>
                <td>5 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Axis Bank</td>
                <td>10.49% - 22.00%</td>
                <td>Up to 2.00%</td>
                <td>5 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Bajaj Finserv</td>
                <td>9.98% - 35.00%</td>
                <td>Up to 3.00%</td>
                <td>5 Years</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>

          <h3>Eligibility Criteria</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> CIBIL score of 750+ for best rates; 700+ for standard approval</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Salaried individuals with minimum monthly income of ₹20,000</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Self-employed professionals with minimum annual income of ₹3,00,000</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Age between 21 and 60 years at loan maturity</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Minimum 2 years of total work experience for salaried applicants</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Low FOIR (Fixed Obligation to Income Ratio) below 50% preferred</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>How to Get the Lowest Interest Rate</h3>
          <div class="steps-grid">
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">1</div>
              <h4>Check Your CIBIL Score</h4>
              <p>A score above 750 qualifies you for the lowest rates. Check your free score on TrueCred before applying.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">2</div>
              <h4>Compare Across Lenders</h4>
              <p>Use our comparison tool to see rates from 80+ lenders side by side. Filter by your income, city, and employer.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">3</div>
              <h4>Choose the Best Offer</h4>
              <p>Select the lender with the lowest effective rate (including processing fee and other charges) for your profile.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">4</div>
              <h4>Apply & Save</h4>
              <p>Apply online through TrueCred for exclusive rate offers and get approval within hours. Track your application in real-time.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Documents Required</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Identity Proof — Aadhaar Card, PAN Card, Passport, or Voter ID</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Address Proof — Aadhaar Card, Utility Bill, Rent Agreement, or Passport</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Income Proof — Latest 3 months salary slips or Form 16 / ITR</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Bank Statements — Last 6 months bank account statements</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Employment Proof — Offer letter, appointment letter, or experience certificate</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Passport-size photographs (2 copies)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-file-signature"></i> Get Best Rate Quote</h3>
            <form class="sidebar-form" onsubmit="return false;">
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Full Name" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="tel" class="form-input" placeholder="Mobile Number" maxlength="10" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <select class="form-input" required>
                  <option value="" disabled selected>Loan Amount</option>
                  <option value="50000">₹50,000</option>
                  <option value="100000">₹1,00,000</option>
                  <option value="200000">₹2,00,000</option>
                  <option value="300000">₹3,00,000</option>
                  <option value="500000">₹5,00,000</option>
                  <option value="1000000">₹10,00,000</option>
                  <option value="2000000">₹20,00,000</option>
                  <option value="3000000">₹30,00,000</option>
                  <option value="4000000">₹40,00,000</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="City" required>
              </div>
              <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-block" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;">
                Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
              </button>
            </form>
          </div>

          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-link"></i> Quick Links</h3>
            <div class="sidebar-links">
              <a href="/pages/business-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Business Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/home-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Home Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/loan-against-property"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Loan Against Property</a>
              <a href="/pages/gold-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Gold Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/education-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Education Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/car-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Car Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-cards"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Credit Cards</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-score"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Credit Score</a>
              <a href="/pages/calculators"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> EMI Calculator</a>
              <a href="/pages/insurance"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Insurance</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">Got Questions?</span>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p>Everything you need to know about personal loan interest rates.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Which bank offers the lowest personal loan interest rate in 2026?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              As of April 2026, Bajaj Finserv offers personal loans starting at 9.98% p.a. for prime customers with a CIBIL score above 800. Among traditional banks, Axis Bank starts at 10.49% and HDFC Bank at 10.50%. The actual rate you receive depends on your credit profile, income, and employer category.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            What factors determine my personal loan interest rate?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Key factors include: CIBIL score (higher is better), monthly income and employer category (MNC/Government get lower rates), existing relationship with the bank, loan amount and tenure, city of residence, age, and your current debt-to-income ratio. A combination of these factors determines the final rate offered to you.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Is a fixed or floating interest rate better for personal loans?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Most personal loans in India come with a fixed interest rate, meaning your EMI stays constant throughout the tenure. This provides predictability in financial planning. Some NBFCs offer floating rate personal loans linked to their benchmark rate — these may start lower but can increase over time. For personal loans with shorter tenures (1-3 years), fixed rates are generally recommended.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Can I get a lower interest rate after taking the loan?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Yes, you can opt for a personal loan balance transfer to another lender offering a lower rate. This involves transferring your outstanding loan amount to a new bank at a reduced interest rate. TrueCred can help you compare balance transfer offers and save on your EMI. Typically, balance transfer makes sense if the rate difference is at least 1.5-2%.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            How much can I save by choosing a lower interest rate?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              On a ₹10 lakh personal loan for 5 years, the difference between 11% and 14% p.a. amounts to approximately ₹95,000 in total interest savings. Even a 0.5% reduction can save ₹15,000-₹25,000 over the loan tenure. This is why comparing rates on TrueCred before applying is so important.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page CTA -->
  <section class="page-content" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-cta">
        <div>
          <h3>Find the Lowest Personal Loan Rate for You</h3>
          <p>Compare rates from 80+ lenders and save up to ₹1.5 lakhs on interest. Free, instant, and no impact on your CIBIL score.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline" style="color:#fff;border:2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.5);padding:14px 32px;font-size:0.95rem;">
          Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->

</BaseLayout>
